            <entry xml:id="entry_ḱem" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ḱem</orth><form type="variant"><orth>ḱepp</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kem</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3844e74"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>настроение</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>mood</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3844e86" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>æ kemi næj<note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (= и. %ijæ ḱeppyl
                                næw%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (= Iron %ijæ ḱeppyl
                                næw%i)</note></quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он не в настроении</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he is not in the mood</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он не в духе</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he is not in the spirit</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3844e120" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>nuri wængæ dær mæ kemi æz næma 'rdæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>до сих пор еще я не пришла в себя</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I still have not come to my senses</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3844e142">
                        <quote>zin ma wæd dæ kemæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пусть не будет тяжело состоянию твоего духа</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>let it not be difficult for your state of mind</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>93</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, из <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3844e164" xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kef</w>
                        <gloss><q>веселье</q></gloss></mentioned>, усвоенного через посредство
                    кавказских языков, замещающих %if%i согласным %ip%i: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3844e172" xml:lang="xmf"><lang/>
                        <w>kepi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3844e177" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>keipi</w>
                        <gloss><q>веселье</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. Для перебоя %ip%i → %im%i
                    ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_Amistol"/> ← %iапостол%i. Выражение %ijæ
                    ḱeppyl næw%i „он не в духе“ отвечает персидскому %ibī kef ast%i с тем же
                    значением.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Probably it is from <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3844e191" xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kef</w>
                        <gloss><q>fun</q></gloss></mentioned>, acquired via Caucasian languages,
                    which replace %if%i by a consonant %ip%i: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3844e199" xml:lang="xmf"><lang/>
                        <w>kepi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3844e204" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>keipi</w>
                        <gloss><q>fun</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. For the alternation %ip%i → %im%i
                    cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_Amistol"/> ← Russian %iапостол%i ‘apostle’.
                    The expression %ijæ ḱeppyl næw%i „he is not in the mood“ is similar to the
                    Persian one %ibī kef ast%i with the same meaning.</etym>
            </entry>
